question_results.context: Pets are allowed in some managed buildings. [BG] A deposit is required to rent an apartment in a managed building. The security deposit can be either equal to one month's rent or more. Fluffy is Tom's cat. Cats are pets. The Olive Garden is a managed building. The monthly rent at the Olive Garden is $2000. Tom will rent an apartment in a managed building if and only if he is allowed to move in with Fluffy, and the security deposit is no more than $1500. 2000$ is more than $1500.
question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Tom is allowed to move in an apartment in The Olive Garden with Fluffy.
question_results.combined_program:
set(auto).
assign(max_seconds, 5).
assign(max_mem, 1024).
# Predicates:
AllowedPet(x, y) ::: Pet x is allowed in building y.
ManagedBuilding(x) ::: x is a managed building.
DepositRequired(x) ::: A deposit is required to rent an apartment in building x.
RentAmount(x, y) ::: The monthly rent for building x is y.
DepositAmount(x, y) ::: The security deposit for building x is y.
DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x) ::: The security deposit for building x is more than one month's rent.
DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ::: The security deposit for building x is equal to one month's rent.
Cat(x) ::: x is a cat.
Pet(x) ::: x is a pet.
Owns(x, y) ::: x owns pet y.
Apartment(x) ::: x is an apartment.
Rent(x, y) ::: Person x rents apartment y.
MoveIn(x, y) ::: Person x moves into building y.
Fluffy(x) ::: x is Fluffy.
Tom(x) ::: x is Tom.
OliveGarden(x) ::: x is the Olive Garden.
MoreThan(x, y) ::: x is greater than y.
LessThan(x, y) ::: x is less than y.

# Premises:
ManagedBuilding(oliveGarden)
RentAmount(oliveGarden, 2000)
∀x (Cat(x) → Pet(x))
Cat(fluffy)
Owns(tom, fluffy)
∀x (ManagedBuilding(x) → DepositRequired(x))
∀x (DepositRequired(x) → (DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) ∨ DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x)))
∀x (DepositGreaterThanOneMonthRent(x) → MoreThan(DepositAmount(x, _), RentAmount(x, _)))
∀x (DepositEqualToOneMonthRent(x) → DepositAmount(x, RentAmount(x, _)))
AllowedPet(fluffy, oliveGarden)
∀x ∀y (Rent(tom, y) ∧ ManagedBuilding(y) → (MoveIn(tom, y) ↔ (AllowedPet(fluffy, y) ∧ LessThan(DepositAmount(y, _), 1500))))
MoreThan(2000, 1500)

# Conclusion:
AllowedPet(fluffy, oliveGarden)
